p: Our estimates are robust with respect to the assumption on the relative transmissibility of DENV by asymptomatic individuals. In scenarios where asymptomatic individuals have a transmission rate of 50% and 100% compared to symptomatic patients [ 11], the estimated average relative reduction of cases, assuming the same ULV induced mosquito mortality (ρ = 40%), was 23.3% (95%CI: 15.1–31.4%) and 22.1% (95%CI: 13.9–30.2%) respectively (see S1 Appendix).
